criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy male and female, aged ≥ 55 years, suffering from primary insomnia according to
             DSM-IV criteria (307.42)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  According to DSM-IV, subjects belonging to the following groups are excluded: 780.59;
             307.45; 307.47; 780.xx (Appendix 2);

          -  Use of benzodiazepines or other hypnotics during the preceding 1 month with a
             frequency of more than 2 times a week and lasting more than 2 weeks;

          -  Severe neurological, psychiatric or sleep disorders;

          -  Other serious diseases;

          -  Taking more than 1/2 l of alcohol, more than 3 cups of coffee or more than 10
             cigarettes per day .

          -  Subjects who need beta blockers as a treatment.
